COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 729, L.D. 1859
1 'Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
2 allocations are made.
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
4 Early Childhood Learning and Development Resource Hub Fund N552
5 Initiative: Provides funding to establish one Social Services Program Manager position and
6 one Social Services Program Specialist II position to establish and administer early
7 childhood learning and development resource hubs effective January 1, 2026 and provides
8 funding for related All Other costs.
9 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
10 POSITIONS - LEGISLATIVE COUNT 2.000 2.000
11 Personal Services $117,785 $247,036
12 All Other $7,256 $7,256
13 __________ __________
14 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $125,041 $254,292
159 Early Childhood Learning and Development Resource Hub Fund N552
16 Initiative: Provides ongoing funding for contracts to operate 2 regional early childhood
17 learning and development resource hubs beginning July 1, 2026.
18 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
19 All Other $0 $750,000
20 __________ __________
21 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $0 $750,000
2128
23 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES,
24 DEPARTMENT OF
25 DEPARTMENT TOTALS 2025-26 2026-27
26
27 GENERAL FUND $125,041 $1,004,292
28 __________ __________
29 DEPARTMENT TOTAL - ALL FUNDS $125,041 $1,004,292
3203 '
31 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
32 number to read consecutively.
33 SUMMARY
3344 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, changes the number
3355 of early childhood learning and development resource hubs to be established from 4 to 2,
3366 delays the date of establishment from November 1, 2025 to July 1, 2026 and changes the
3377 starting date of the Department of Health and Human Services' annual report to the
3388 Legislature to January 1, 2028. It clarifies that the department must seek input from the
3399 Maine Children's Cabinet Early Childhood Advisory Council rather than the Children's
4400 Cabinet in establishing the resource hubs. It changes the date that the department reports
4411 its plans for establishing the resource hubs to the Joint Standing Committee on Health and
Page 2 - 132LR2207(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 729, L.D. 1859
412 Human Services from December 2025 to March 2026. It updates the appropriations and
423 allocations section.
434 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
445 (See attached)
